column2: Independent and capable of organizing life. A tendency toward self-centeredness. A desire for self-expression in specific areas of life.
Receptive to other people and sensitive to the undercurrents involved in relationships.
An objective, rather than personal, outlook on relationships. A desire for public involvement and a role in society.
A drive to make a mark on the world. This can be beneficial, but could become disruptive if overly caught up in an ideal.
